From: Red Team <red@superma>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 01:39:46 +0800
Subject: [PATCH R-001] Fix silent message drop when WebSocket closes between
 canSend check and send() call

Problem: TOCTOU race between canSend guard in ChatInput.handleSend() and
WebSocket.send() in useChat().send(). If WS disconnects between these,
user text is cleared but message never delivered.

Fix:
- useChat().send() returns boolean indicating delivery success
- useChatInput.send() propagates the boolean
- ChatView.onSend() propagates the boolean  
- ChatInput.handleSend() checks return value, shows connectionError banner
  and preserves text on failure instead of silently dropping

---
 web/src/components/ChatInput.vue    | 15 ++++++++++++++-
 web/src/composables/useChat.ts       |  5 +++--
 web/src/composables/useChatInput.ts  | 11 ++++++-----
 web/src/views/ChatView.vue          |  5 +++--
 4 files changed, 26 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/web/src/components/ChatInput.vue b/web/src/components/ChatInput.vue
index af578c1..38fdc61 100644
